headline: Week’s Best: Fidelity’s Cash-Sweep Play
summary: Fidelity Investments is changing its policy on cash holdings so that more of clients’ uninvested funds wind up in a low-interest sweep account.  Starting next year, Fidelity will put cash held in nonretirement brokerage accounts in its FCash product, which pays an interest rate less than half of some money-market accounts.  The move applies to grandfathered accounts overseen by independent financial advisors that had previously been exempt from the cash-sweep policy Fidelity announced a year ago.
